      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/claim/vad-hemolysis-model-adequate",
      "type": "Claim",
      "name": "CFD model predicts absolute hemolysis index below clinical threshold across all VAD operating conditions",
      "description": "The CFD hemolysis model, employing the Giersiepen-Wurzinger power-law formulation coupled with Lagrangian particle tracking, produces absolute Hemolysis Index (HI) predictions that remain below the 0.8% absolute clinical threshold across all five evaluated flow-speed operating points (3–6 L/min, 2400–3600 RPM). Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification (N=5000, Latin Hypercube Sampling) yields a 95th-percentile HI of 0.61%, providing a margin of 0.19% against the acceptance criterion. The model is therefore judged adequate for the stated context of use. This claim is supported by the validation activities documented in the accompanying ValidationResult nodes and by the credibility factor assessments recorded herein.",
      "scope": "FDA generic centrifugal blood pump geometry; VAD operating envelope; absolute hemolysis prediction; Class III device submission context",
      "purpose": "Provide the central credibility assertion that the CFD model output is fit for use as primary evidence for hemolysis acceptance in a PMA submission"
    }
  ],
