    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "The credibility assessment team concludes that the CFD hemolysis model is accepted for the stated context of use based on the central claim (https://uofa.net/synth/claim/vad-hemolysis-model-adequate), which asserts that predicted HI remains below the 0.8% clinical threshold with a 95th-percentile value of 0.61% under Monte Carlo UQ. The claim is richly described and contextually coherent with the four ValidationResult nodes, which individually carry full provenance chains to experimental and computational evidence. Credibility factor gaps at MRL 5 are acknowledged; the team judges that the conservative over-prediction bias (8–14%) and the UQ margin provide sufficient confidence for submission purposes.",
    "decidedAt": "2026-04-19T00:00:00Z"
  },
